# Java Backend Standards

## Style

- Java 21 toolchain; use records/value objects for immutable DTOs where appropriate
- Lombok: `@Data`, `@NoArgsConstructor`, `@AllArgsConstructor` on entities; `@RequiredArgsConstructor` on services
- Constructor injection only — no `@Autowired` on fields

## Layering

```java
// ✅ Controller — validation + HTTP mapping only
@PostMapping("/conversations/{id}/messages")
public ApiResponse<ChatExchangeResponse> sendMessage(
        @PathVariable UUID id, @Valid @RequestBody SendMessageRequest request) {
    return ApiResponse.ok(chatService.sendMessage(id, request));
}

// ✅ Service — owns @Transactional and business logic
@Transactional
public ChatExchangeResponse sendMessage(UUID id, SendMessageRequest request) { ... }

// ❌ BAD — controller calling repository or ChatModel directly
```

## New Files Checklist

- DTO → `chat/dto/` with Jakarta validation annotations
- Exception → `common/exception/` + handler in `GlobalExceptionHandler`
- Config property → `application.yml` + field in `AiosProperties`
- DB table → `V{n}__description.sql` + entity + repository

## Testing

- Smoke test: `@SpringBootTest` with `@ActiveProfiles("test")`
- Run `.\gradlew.bat build` (Windows) or `./gradlew build` before completing
